<subSubSection id="C1826517073DFF92FCECF89E6F924EE5" pageId="17" pageNumber="250" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8927369C073DFF92FCECF89E68BC41D1" blockId="17.[794,1393,1895,2318]" pageId="17" pageNumber="250">
<emphasis id="BBECEA8E073DFF92FCECF89E68B54186" bold="true" box="[799,954,1895,1924]" pageId="17" pageNumber="250">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F073DFF92FC1CF89E686B41AE" authority="Thomas, 1892" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1892" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Geomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="17" pageNumber="250" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bulleri">Geomys bulleri Thomas, 1892</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="39F03CC1073DFF92FC8FF86A68BC41D1" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3799834316" pageId="17" pageNumber="250">“Talpa, Mascota, Jalisco [Mexico], 8500 feet.”</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8927369C073DFF92FCD3F8206F924EE5" blockId="17.[794,1393,1895,2318]" pageId="17" pageNumber="250">
Molecular studies suggest that the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F073DFF92FCD3F7FC68CA4E20" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1895" box="[800,965,2053,2082]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Pappogeomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="17" pageNumber="250" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pappogeomys</taxonomicName>
1s sister to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F073DFF92FACFF7FC68824E4B" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1895" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Cratogeomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="17" pageNumber="250" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Cratogeomys</taxonomicName>
. The subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F073DFF92FB76F7D56FD34E4B" authorityName="Russell" authorityYear="1957" box="[1157,1244,2092,2121]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Pappogeomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="17" pageNumber="250" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alcorni">alcorni</taxonomicName>
was previously recognized at the species level but was regarded as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4E984D1F073DFF92FB05F78E6E4B4E9A" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1892" box="[1270,1348,2167,2200]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Geomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="17" pageNumber="250" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bulleri">bulleri</taxonomicName>
by J. W. Demastes and colleagues in 2003. Five subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
